{{use dmy dates|date=July 2016}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = BOL | NOCname = [[Bolivian Olympic Committee]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1992 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.cobol.org.bo }}&nbsp;{{es icon}} | location = [[Barcelona]] | competitors = 13 (8 men, 5 women) | sports = 6 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Bolivia]]''' competed at the '''[[1992 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]. Thirteen competitors, eight men and five women, took part in eighteen events in six sports.<ref name="SportsRef">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/BOL/summer/1992/ |title=Bolivia at the 1992 Summer Games |accessdate=29 July 2016 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref>
==Athletics== {{main|Athletics at the 1992 Summer Olympics}}
'''Men's 5,000 metres''' *[[Policarpio Calizaya]] ** Heat &mdash; 15:02.02 (→ did not advance)
'''Men's 10,000 metres''' *[[Policarpio Calizaya]] ** Heat &mdash; 30:27.01 (→ did not advance)
'''Men's Marathon''' * [[Juan Camacho (Bolivian athlete)|Juan Camacho]] &mdash; 2:26.01 (→ 57th place)
'''Women's 200 metres''' * [[Jacqueline Soliz]] ** Heat &mdash; did not advance
'''Women's 400 metres''' * [[Jacqueline Soliz]] ** Heat &mdash; did not advance
'''Women's 10,000 metres''' *[[Sandra Cortez]] ** Heat &mdash; did not start (→ did not advance)
'''Women's 4x400 metres Relay''' * [[Jacqueline Soliz]], [[Sandra Antelo]], [[Gloria Burgos]], and [[Moré Galetovic]] ** Heat &mdash; did not advance
==Cycling== {{main|Cycling at the 1992 Summer Olympics}} One male cyclists represented Bolivia in 1992.
;[[Cycling at the 1992 Summer Olympics – Men's sprint|Men's sprint]] * [[Pedro Vaca]]
;[[Cycling at the 1992 Summer Olympics – Men's 1 km time trial|Men's 1 km time trial]] * [[Pedro Vaca]]
