{{Infobox venue | name = Fengshan Stadium | nickname = | native_name = 高雄市立鳳山體育場 | native_name_lang = zh | fullname = | former names = Kaohsiung County Stadium | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Fengshan Stadium, Kaohsiung City.jpg | image_size = 250px | image_alt = | caption = | pushpin_map = Kaohsiung | pushpin_mapsize = 250px | pushpin_map_caption = Taiwan | pushpin_label_position = | pushpin_relief = yes | address = | location = [[Fengshan District|Fengshan]], [[Kaohsiung]], [[Taiwan]] | coordinates = {{Coord|22|37|18.5|N|120|21|16.2|E|display=inline,title}} | type = [[Stadium]] | genre = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1976 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | production = | cost = | architect = | builder = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = 18,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | publictransit = [[Fongshan MRT station|Fongshan Station]] }}
The '''Fengshan Stadium, Kaohsiung City''' ({{zh|c=高雄市立鳳山體育場|p=Gāoxióng Shìlì Fèngshān Tǐyùchǎng}}), formerly known as '''Kaohsiung County Stadium''' (高雄縣立體育場), is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Fengshan District]], [[Kaohsiung]], [[Taiwan]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and serves as the home venue of [[Taiwan Power Company F.C.|Taipower]]. The stadium is able to hold 18,000 people and was opened in 1976.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ks.edu.tw/stadium/ |title=高雄市鳳山體育場 |publisher=Ks.edu.tw |date=1998-02-28 |accessdate=2014-05-25}}</ref>
==Transportation== The stadium is accessible within walking distance South from [[Fongshan MRT station|Fongshan Station]] of the [[Kaohsiung MRT]].
