[[File:Quinnel Brown.png|thumb|right|150px|Express forward [[Quinnel Brown]] currently holds the award.]]
The '''National Basketball League of Canada Most Valuable Player''' (MVP) is an annual [[National Basketball League of Canada]] award given since the league's inaugural [[2011–12 NBL Canada season|2011–12]] season for the best performing player in the regular season. The winner, along with those of the other major awards, are nominated by the NBL Canada coaches.<ref>{{cite web|title=NBL CANADA ANNOUNCES 2013-2014 AWARD WINNERS|url=http://www.rainmenbasketball.ca/p/14513/nr/100080/nbl-canada-announces-2013-2014-award-winners|website=''RainmenBasketball.ca''|accessdate=4 May 2015}}</ref> As of May 2015, the current holder is [[Quinnel Brown]], a [[forward (basketball)|forward]] for the [[Windsor Express]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Duff|first1=Bob|title=Express forward Quinnel Brown selected MVP of the NBL of Canada|url=http://blogs.windsorstar.com/sports/express-forward-brown-is-nbl-canada-mvp|website=[[The Windsor Star]]|accessdate=4 May 2015}}</ref> Every player that has been named MVP has come from the [[United States]], and none have won it multiple times.<ref>{{cite web|title=Canadian NBL Season MVP Recipients|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/international/league/74/Canadian-NBL/awards/by_type/Canadian-NBL-Season-MVP/340|website=''[[RealGM]]''|accessdate=4 May 2015}}</ref>

